Woods Hole, June 1988
C. elegans bibliography
Reviews:
1. Wood, W.B. 1988 The Nematode Caenorhabditis elegans. Cold
Spring Harbor Laboratory. New York.
2. Sternberg, P.W. and H.R. Horvitz 1984 The genetic control of
cell lineage during nematode development. Ann. Rev. Genetics 18,
489 - 524.
3. Emmons, S. 1987 Mechanisms of Q; elegans development. Cell
51, 881-883.
4. Hodgkin, J. 1987a Sex determination and dosage compensation
in Caenorhabditis elegans. Ann. Rev. Genetics. 21, 133-154.
5. Kenyon, C. (1988) The nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
Science 240, 1448-1453.
Description of nematode cell lineages: -
1. Suston, J.E. and Horvitz, H.R. 1977 Postembryonic cell
lineages of the nematode Q; elegans. Dev. Biol. 56, 110 - 156.
2. Kimble, J. and Hirsh, D. 1979 cell lineages of
the hermaphrodtie and male gonads in Q; elegans. Dev. Biol. 70,
396 - 417.
3. Sulston J.E. Schierenberg, E., White, J.G., and Thomson, J.N.
1983 The embryonic cell lineage of the nematode Q; elegans. Dev.
Biol. 100, 64 - 119.
Blastomere isolation and defect experiments:
1. Sulston, J.E. and White, J.G. 1980 Regulation and cell
autonomy' during* postembryonic development of Qg  elegans. Dev.
Biol. 78, 577 - 597.
2. Laufer, J.S., Bazzicalupo, P. and Wood, W.B. 1980 Segregation
of developmental potential in early embryos of Q; elegans. Cell
19. 569-577. 
3. Kimble, J. 1981 Lineage alterations after ablation of cells
in the somatic gonad of Q; elegans. Dev. Biol. 87, 286 - 300.
4. Kimble, J. and White, J.G. 1981 On the control of germ cell
development in Q; elegans. Dev. Biol. 81, 208 - 219.
5. Sternberg, P.W. and Horvitz, H.R. 1986 Pattern formation
during vulval development in Q; elegans Cell 44, 761-772.
6. Priess, J.R. and Thomson, J.N. 1987 Cellular interactions in
early Q; elegans embryos. Cell 48, 241-250.
Lineage mutants: 
1. Chalfie, M. IL Robert Horvitz, and JT. E. Suston 1981
Mutations that lead to reiterations in the cell lineages of 
elegans. Cell 24, 59-69.
2. Ferguson, E.L. and Horvitz, H.R. 1985 Identification and
characterization of 22 genes that affect the vulval cell lineages
of QL elegans. Genetics 110, 17 - 72.
3. Ferguson, E.L., Sternberg, P.W. and Horvitz, H.R. 1987 A
genetic pathway for the specification of the vulval cell lineages
of Q; elegans. Nature 326, 259-267.
